{
  "stem": "7506.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't mean it in that way, but people that could be possibly of use to the German Reich.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we had our own clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were together.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the first, I would say, weeks in the camp, it really wasn't very much different to being in Westerburg, only in the sense that I never saw any transports go out of Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I never saw any trains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I never saw a railway track.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The railway track I saw is the one we arrived at.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But after that, I never in the camp, I never saw any trains moving about.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I felt while I was in Belsen in the early days, I felt that it sort of agreed with what my mother said to me, That.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe we're going to be exchanged.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe we're going to be sent to England.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe we're going to be sent to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I dare say at that time, I felt almost, if I could use the word, which seems a strange word now, a sense of well-being, somewhat of safety.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because I felt that we were going to go to England to my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I must have lived somehow with that hope those days, those early days in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But things started to deteriorate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not long after we were there, we had to go on appell.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Every day we had to go and appell.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Normally, it was early in the day, early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We would be ordered out of the barracks by Jewish people, Dutch Jewish people, with either armband or something on their chest here.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But also the Germans, the SS present, we would be ordered out of the barracks in fast fashion to go to the appellplatz.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
